# CODEOWNERS — defines required reviewers for changes to specific paths.
# Reference: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositories-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
#
# Pattern matching is similar to .gitignore. The LAST matching pattern wins
# for any given path, so order matters.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Framework — foundational constraints (legal, operational, accounting,
# mission/vision/values). Modifications must be approved by the Head of
# Product, since these documents reflect the structural reality of the
# group and changing them affects every product.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
/framework/                @a1yr

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Repository governance — README, CODEOWNERS, CONTRIBUTING, .gitignore.
# Changes here affect how the entire team works against the repository.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
/README.md                 @a1yr
/CODEOWNERS                @a1yr
/CONTRIBUTING.md           @a1yr
/.gitignore                @a1yr
